^-{ ^*BDeal of the Week 311 - August 26, 2002^*N
^*BBy Fred Gitelman^*N }
^-
I am proud to report that this week's deal was played by my partner, ^*BBrad Moss^*N, in an early round Spingold match at this year's ACBL Summer Nationals in Washington DC.

The 2002 World Championships are being played now in Montreal, Canada. So far my results in this tournament have been exceptionally poor, but hopefully Brad and I will do well in the World Open Pairs (which started August 25). As you will understand when you see how well Brad played this week's deal, I hope I have a lot of opporunties to be the dummy in this event!

Even if my lack of success at this tournament continues, I expect to have plenty of interesting deals from Montreal to report in upcoming ^*BDeals of the Week^*N!

The big news so far from Montreal is that my friends ^*BBill Gates^*N and ^*BSharon Osberg^*N played in the World Mixed Pairs. Bill held a press conference (about bridge) in Montreal which took place in a large room full of cameras and reporters. I had never seen anything like this at a bridge tournament before - the media tends to ignore even the biggest bridge tournaments.

Bill said a whole bunch of great things about bridge in front of the cameras. As a result, the game received a lot of positive media coverage all over the world. This is exactly the sort of advertising that bridge needs - a highly respected and very famous person telling the world about his love for our remarkable game. Thanks Bill!

