On this web page, there is a story about Bill in Montreal and links to 2 video clips. These video clips (which were shown on TV across Canada) contain scenes from Bill's press conference and interviews with bridge players in Montreal (unfortunately some of these do not have a very good sense of marketing). I am interviewed briefly in both video clips as well.

The process of getting interviewed in front of a camera is interesting. The interview generally lasts about 20 minutes and the reporter spends all of this time asking you questions. Frequently the same question is asked several different times (sometimes in a slightly different way). All of this is condensed to 10 seconds or so and it can be amusing to see which 10 seconds of the 20 minutes appears on the air. 

